  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (3a462eb 2022-09-22T03:37:08.364254Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nnot sure if this qualifies as a \"bug\" but I think it's worth discussing. Example cmd/output below for reference\r\n\r\n```\r\nλ forge script script/Script.s.sol:MyScript --rpc-url $RPC_URL -vvvv\r\n[⠰] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\nTraces:\r\n  [x] MyScript::run()\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::envUint(PRIVATE_KEY)\r\n    │   └─ ← {{ leaked }}\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::startBroadcast({{ leaked }})\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [x] → new MyFactory@address\r\n    │   ├─ [x] → new MyImpl@address\r\n    │   │   └─ ← x bytes of code\r\n    │   └─ ← x bytes of code\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::stopBroadcast()\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\n\r\nScript ran successfully.\r\n==========================\r\nSimulated On-chain Traces:\r\n\r\n  [x] Create2Deployer::create2()\r\n    ├─ [x] → new MyFactory@address\r\n    │   ├─ [x] → new MyImpl@address\r\n    │   │   └─ ← x bytes of code\r\n    │   └─ ← x bytes of code\r\n    └─ ← address\r\n```\r\n\r\nideally there would be a way to get the trace w/o logging `privKey` to term? but maybe .. maybe these deploy scripts just shouldn't be run w `-vvvv`\r\n\r\n(I've always thought having sensitive information in the terminal was less secure than inside a e.g. `.env` but as I'm thinking about it now if someone has access to your terminal screen / output they probably have access to your `.env`? arguably the main downside is the logs might be stored for a long time and searched later, whereas presumably you don't keep your `privKey` stored for a long period of time, only when in use)",
